MTN has published its integrated report for 2019, showing what its top executives were paid in the last year. MTN group chief financial officer, Ralph Mupita, took home the largest salary at the group in 2019, earning R66.3 million for the year. This includes a basic salary of R9.15 million, other benefits of R43.8 million (including R42 million paid out as part of an incentive scheme), and a R13.4 million bonus. Group chief executive officer, Rob Shuter took home a salary of R58.23 million, including a basic salary of R17.3 million and a R27.6 million bonus. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-386351" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-exec-salaries-2019.png" alt="" width="1142" height="445" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-exec-salaries-2019.png 1142w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-exec-salaries-2019-300x117.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-exec-salaries-2019-1024x399.png 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-exec-salaries-2019-768x299.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> Including executive directors and prescribed officers, MTN paid a total of R292.2 million in salaries to its 12 top executives in 2019. Of this, prescribed officers accounted for R167.7 million. The table below outlines how they were paid. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-386349" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-officer-salaries.png" alt="" width="1135" height="506" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-officer-salaries.png 1135w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-officer-salaries-300x134.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-officer-salaries-1024x457.png 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-officer-salaries-768x342.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 1362px) 62vw, 840px" /> Split across a year (365 days), the average executive earns R49,950 a day – with Shuter and Mupita earning R159,550 and R181,650 a day, respectively. The table below outlines how these salaries a split per day: Financial performance Earlier in March, MTN reported a healthy rise in revenue for the year ended December 2019, despite challenging macroeconomic conditions, particularly in South Africa. The group also announced that Shuter will be stepping down at the end of his contract in March 2021. The group reported revenue growth of 9.7% to R151.5 billion, with MTN South Africa revenue almost unchanged at R36.43 billion. Reported headline earnings per share (HEPS) were 468 cents, from 337 cents in December 2018. Highlights Subscribers increased by 18.2 million to 251 million;
Revenue grew by 9.7%;
Service revenue grew by 9.8%;
IFRS reported EBITDA (before once-off items) increased by 34.3%;
Final dividend of 355 cents per share in line with guidance. The group added 18 million customers to reach a total of 251 million and increased data users by 17 million to 95 million and fintech customers by 7 million to 35 million. In constant currency terms, group service revenue increased by 9.8% to R141.8 billion and earnings before interest, tax, depreciation and amortisation (EBITDA) expanded by 13.6% to R53.4 billion. MTN’s share price has tanked in recent sessions – halving in value over the past month alone. MTN finance chief Ralph Mupita has blamed trade momentum and not intrinsic value for the decline in the group’s  share price in recent months. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-386367" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-1.png" alt="" width="727" height="393" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-1.png 727w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/MTN-1-300x162.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> Read: MTN announces massive price cuts and free data 